# BD Architect Project Initialization

## Overview
Complete workflow for initializing a new project with BD Architect standards. Automates project setup including levels, views, sheets, and keynote linking.

## When to Use
- Starting a new project
- User says "start new project", "initialize project", "new BD project"
- Setting up a project from template
- Need to apply BD Architect standards to a new model

## Prerequisites
- Revit open with new document (from BD Architect template)
- RevitMCPBridge connected
- Project type determined (healthcare, residential, commercial)

---

## PIPELINE: BD Project Initialization

### PHASE 1: Gather Project Information
**Checkpoint: User confirms project details**

```
Step 1.1: Determine project type
  Options:
  - healthcare: AHCA compliant, multi-level, demo/new phases
  - residential: Single/multi-family, hurricane code compliance
  - commercial: Tenant improvement, landlord coordination

Step 1.2: Get project details
  Required:
  - projectNumber: e.g., "2-151" (healthcare) or "1-234" (residential)
  - projectName: e.g., "BHN CATH SUITES PHASE 2"
  Optional:
  - clientName: e.g., "Baptist Health Network"
  - address: e.g., "123 Main Street, Miami, FL"
  - customLevels: Override default levels

Step 1.3: Confirm with user
  Display: Project type, number, name, default level config
  Allow: User to modify before proceeding
```

### PHASE 2: Execute Project Initialization
**Checkpoint: Confirm Revit is ready**

```
Step 2.1: Initialize project
  Tool: RevitMCP.initializeBDAProject({
    projectType: "<selected>",
    projectNumber: "<number>",
    projectName: "<name>",
    clientName: "<client>",
    address: "<address>",
    createViews: true,
    createSheets: true,
    linkKeynotes: true
  })

  This performs:
  1. Set project information
  2. Create standard levels (if not present)
  3. Create standard views for each level
  4. Create standard sheet set
  5. Link BD Architect keynote file

Step 2.2: Verify results
  Output will contain:
  - levels: Array of created/existing levels
  - views: Array of created views
  - sheets: Array of created sheets
  - keynotes: Link status
  - codeRequirements: Applicable codes
  - specialConsiderations: Project-specific notes
```

### PHASE 3: Post-Setup Verification
**Checkpoint: User reviews created elements**

```
Step 3.1: Run initial checklist
  Tool: RevitMCP.runProjectChecklist({
    checklistType: "SD"
  })

  Checks:
  - Levels exist
  - Floor plans created
  - Project info complete

Step 3.2: Report to user
  Display:
  - Number of levels created
  - Number of views created
  - Number of sheets created
  - Keynote link status
  - Checklist results
  - Any items requiring manual attention

Step 3.3: Suggest next steps
  Based on project type:
  - Healthcare: Set up ICRA notes, phase views
  - Residential: Import site survey, set up roof levels
  - Commercial: Coordinate with landlord specs
```

---

## Default Level Configurations

### Healthcare
| Level | Elevation |
|-------|-----------|
| Level 1 | 0'-0" |
| Level 2 | 14'-0" |

### Residential
| Level | Elevation |
|-------|-----------|
| First Floor | 0'-0" |
| Second Floor | 10'-0" |
| Roof | 20'-0" |

### Commercial
| Level | Elevation |
|-------|-----------|
| Level 1 | 0'-0" |

---

## Standard Sheet Sets

### Healthcare
- A-000: Cover Sheet
- A-001: General Notes & Abbreviations
- A-002: Code Analysis
- A-003: Life Safety Plan
- A-100: Demolition Plan
- A-101: Floor Plan - Level 1
- A-102: Floor Plan - Level 2
- A-200: Reflected Ceiling Plan - Level 1
- A-201: Reflected Ceiling Plan - Level 2
- A-300: Interior Elevations
- A-400: Enlarged Plans
- A-500: Wall Sections
- A-501: Building Sections
- A-600: Details
- A-700: Door Schedule
- A-701: Finish Schedule

### Residential
- A-001: Site Plan
- A-002: General Notes
- A-101: First Floor Plan
- A-102: Second Floor Plan
- A-103: Roof Plan
- A-201: Exterior Elevations
- A-301: Building Section
- A-401: Wall Sections
- A-501: Details
- A-601: Door & Window Schedules

### Commercial
- A-001: General Notes & Abbreviations
- A-100: Existing Conditions
- A-101: Demolition Plan
- A-102: Floor Plan
- A-200: Reflected Ceiling Plan
- A-300: Interior Elevations
- A-400: Details
- A-500: Schedules

---

## Individual MCP Methods Available

### initializeBDAProject
Full project initialization with all standards.

### createStandardViews
Create views only (if project already has levels).
```json
{
  "projectType": "healthcare"
}
```

### createStandardSheetSet
Create sheet set only.
```json
{
  "projectType": "healthcare",
  "includeEmpty": true
}
```

### linkKeynoteFile
Link BD Architect keynotes.
```json
{
  "keynoteFilePath": "D:\\BDArchitect-DetailLibrary-2025\\templates\\KEYNOTES - ALL.txt"
}
```

### runProjectChecklist
Run phase checklist for quality verification.
```json
{
  "checklistType": "SD" | "DD" | "CD" | "QC"
}
```

---

## Code Requirements by Project Type

### Healthcare
- Authority: AHCA (Agency for Health Care Administration)
- Building Code: Florida Building Code
- Fire Code: NFPA 101 Life Safety Code
- Accessibility: ADA / ANSI A117.1
- Healthcare Specific: AHCA 59A-3, FGI Guidelines

### Residential
- Authority: Local Building Department
- Building Code: Florida Building Code - Residential
- Accessibility: Fair Housing Act (multi-family)
- Energy Code: Florida Energy Code

### Commercial
- Authority: Local Building Department
- Building Code: Florida Building Code
- Fire Code: NFPA 101 Life Safety Code
- Accessibility: ADA / ANSI A117.1

---

## Special Considerations

### Healthcare Projects
- ICRA (Infection Control Risk Assessment)
- Medical Gas Systems
- Nurse Call Systems
- Fire/Smoke Compartments (22,500 SF max)
- Clean/Soiled Workflow
- Patient Privacy (HIPAA)

### Residential Projects
- Hurricane Protection (Miami-Dade NOA)
- Wind Load Requirements
- Flood Zone Compliance
- HOA Requirements (if applicable)
- Setback Requirements

### Commercial Projects
- Landlord Requirements
- Base Building Coordination
- Existing Conditions Verification
- After-Hours Work Requirements
- Tenant Signage Requirements

---

## Example Usage

```
User: "Start a new healthcare project"

Claude:
1. Ask for project number and name
2. Confirm project type is healthcare
3. Show default level configuration
4. Execute initializeBDAProject
5. Report results
6. Run SD checklist
7. Suggest next steps (set up demo views, ICRA notes)
```

